  "prompt": "Was Khizr Khan paid over 100k by CNN and NBC and 175k by the DNC?",
  "response": "There have been claims circulating online suggesting that Khizr Khan, the Gold Star father who spoke at the 2016 Democratic National Convention, was paid significant sums by CNN, NBC, and the Democratic National Committee (DNC). However, these claims are not supported by evidence.\n\nIn 2017, fact-checking website Snopes investigated these claims and found them to be false. The claims appear to have originated from an unreliable source and were not backed by any credible financial disclosures or official records.\n\nKhizr Khan did indeed receive widespread media attention following his speech at the DNC, and he appeared on various news networks, including CNN and NBC. However, there is no evidence to suggest that he was paid over $100,000 by either network or $175,000 by the DNC.\n\nIt's essential to approach such claims with skepticism and verify information through reputable sources before accepting them as true.",
